<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">138 Emergency Program/759a:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-25T17:00:00-05:00">March
                                        25, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. With reference to the Department’s telegrams of November 17, 6
                                p.m. and November 22, 6 p.m., 1939,<note n="4" xml:id="d58fn4">
                                    <ref target="frus1939v01#pg_706">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 706</ref> and <ref target="frus1939v01#pg_709">709</ref>, respectively.</note>
                                the Department desires that no passport be validated for the journey
                                through the combat zone of the North Atlantic en route to the United
                                States without permission being first obtained from the
                                Department.</p>
                            <p>Please so inform offices in Europe.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>